    {
      "author": "Andrew Stone",
      "text": "LSA flooding of bandwidth is also going to have a downstream effect on BGP-LS if it's in use as well",
      "time": "2026-07-23T15:35:23.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "Jie Dong",
      "text": "@Andrew do you mean the link bandwith utilization information will also need to be reported in BGP-LS?",
      "time": "2026-07-23T15:40:52.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "Tony Li",
      "text": "LSA/LSP flooding of bandwidth has been a solved problem since 1998.",
      "time": "2026-07-23T15:43:52.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "David Lamparter",
      "text": "Feels like there's some confusion between bandwidth and utilization?",
      "time": "2026-07-23T15:45:35.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "Boris Khasanov",
      "text": "Would be helpful to hear Jeff's comments on the GSE  credit-based approach",
      "time": "2026-07-23T15:47:53.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "Jie Dong",
      "text": "@David in the draft of the previous presentation, both the link bandwidth and the actual used bandwidth are advertised",
      "time": "2026-07-23T15:49:57.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "Tony Li",
      "text": "Which is what TE has always done.",
      "time": "2026-07-23T15:50:15.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "Jeff Tantsura",
      "text": "Looks a bit like IB :)",
      "time": "2026-07-23T15:50:22.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "Tony Li",
      "text": "Bandwidth and utilization are just a few ops different and are functionally interchageable.",
      "time": "2026-07-23T15:50:50.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "Tony Li",
      "text": "https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-farinacci-lisp-satellite-network/",
